\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Explain why these are the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

largest
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

smallest
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 possible 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebras, respectively, in the following sense: if 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal A}$
\end_inset

 is any 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebra, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \emptyset,X\right\} \subset{\cal A}\subset{\cal P}(X)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
