\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula $\Question$
\end_inset

Prove: If 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in\mathscr{L}^{1}(\mu,E)$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is finite almost everywhere on 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\Answer$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{n}\coloneqq f^{-1}((n,\infty))$
\end_inset

.
 Then we know that 
\begin_inset Formula $n\mu(E_{n})\leq\i f{E_{n}}{}{\mu}$
\end_inset

.
 Then:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\mu(E_{n}) & \leq & \frac{1}{n}\i f{E_{n}}{}{\mu}\\
 & \leq & \frac{1}{n}\i fE{}{\mu}.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Also, 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{n\to\infty}\mu(E_{n})\to0$
\end_inset

 because 
\begin_inset Formula $\i fE{}{\mu}<\infty$
\end_inset

.
 Next, since
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f^{-1}(\left\{ \infty\right\} )=\bigcap_{n=1}^{\infty}E_{n},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{n+1}\subset E_{n}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, and that there is an 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(E_{N})<\infty$
\end_inset

, then by 
\emph on
continuity from above
\emph default
 we have that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu(f^{-1}(\left\{ \infty\right\} ))=\lim_{n\to\infty}\mu(E_{n})=0.
\]

\end_inset

Thus, it follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 must be finite everywhere, except on a set of measure zero; i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is finite almost everywhere.
\begin_inset Formula $\hfill\blacksquare$
\end_inset


\end_layout

